**Which test(s) are flaking**:

pkg/scheduler unit tests occasionally timeout at 5 minutes

**Reason for failure**:

Stats from 10 runs of the package:
```
Stats over 10 runs: max = 315.3s, min = 30.9s, avg = 67.0s, dev = 83.0s
```

The average (excluding the run that timed out) is ~40 seconds. The run that timed out took at least 5 minutes before being killed. That smells like a deadlock / failure-to-progress scenario which could be a real bug.

Our presubmit CI runs tolerate flakes, retrying 3 times and passing on a single success, which is masking this issue.

Observed in https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/pull/93605#issuecomment-668127993 which is turning off that toleration and exercising every unit test package 10 times to ensure consistent passes:

```
//pkg/scheduler

TIMEOUT: //pkg/scheduler:go_default_test (Summary)
      /bazel-scratch/.cache/bazel/_bazel_root/7989b31489f31aee54f32688da2f0120/execroot/io_k8s_kubernetes/bazel-out/k8-fastbuild/testlogs/pkg/scheduler/go_default_test/run_8_of_10/test.log
```
https://prow.k8s.io/view/gs/kubernetes-jenkins/pr-logs/pull/93605/pull-kubernetes-bazel-test/1290315521706692610

```
//pkg/scheduler:go_default_test                                         TIMEOUT in 1 out of 10 in 315.3s
  Stats over 10 runs: max = 315.3s, min = 30.9s, avg = 67.0s, dev = 83.0s
```
https://prow.k8s.io/view/gs/kubernetes-jenkins/pr-logs/pull/93605/pull-kubernetes-bazel-test/1290996656451358721

```
TIMEOUT: //pkg/scheduler:go_default_test (Summary)
      /bazel-scratch/.cache/bazel/_bazel_root/7989b31489f31aee54f32688da2f0120/execroot/io_k8s_kubernetes/bazel-out/k8-fastbuild/testlogs/pkg/scheduler/go_default_test/run_5_of_10/test.log
INFO: From Testing //pkg/scheduler:go_default_test (run 5 of 10):
```

https://prow.k8s.io/view/gs/kubernetes-jenkins/pr-logs/pull/93605/pull-kubernetes-bazel-test/1292167859186700288


I can reproduce this by building the unit test package with:
```
go test -race -c ./pkg/scheduler
```

and then running repeatedly with `stress`:

this appears to hang increasing numbers of parallel runs on the deadlock until timeouts are hit:
